<p>In conclusion, injuries in college football are, as they say, part of the game. The ability to come back from such injuries is also what helps players have successful careers and, perhaps, go on to professional careers. There have been many advances in athletic training that help players get back on the field quickly and safely in most cases. While very few recover in the amazing way Amari Rodgers did, the data shows that injuries will occur, but techniques to help players recover will keep pace with these challenges. The data also suggests that more emphasis can be given to the most common injuries to help prevent them from occurring in the first place.</p>